• Stakeholder clarity: I’m practiced at translating ambiguous asks into crisp specs, aligning stakeholders quickly, and documenting decisions to keep pace high.
• Quality under speed: I use lightweight checklists/QA to avoid rework while moving fast (clear acceptance criteria, small milestones, early demos).

Two quick questions: (1) Is there a single non-negotiable requirement I still clearly don’t meet (so I can stop pursuing respectfully), or is it more a relative ranking versus other candidates? (2) If it’s relative ranking, is there any additional evidence (work sample, reference, short exercise) that could realistically change the decision?
